rooms.Name: Spam Square
rooms.Description:
This is spam square.  The center of The Land of lag.  You can barely
moven in here because of all of the phrases and movements people are making.
To the East is the theater and a small cafe.  To the west is city hall, the
police station and the Lagmaster's guild.

rooms.Name: The Temple of The Lag Gods
rooms.Description:
A massive marble temple with a golden alter in the center of it.  People
bow before the temple and worship deeply.  They come here to beg the lag
Gods for mercy and to stop lagging their computers.  To the North is Lag
Square and to the south is the main exit to The Land of Lag.  To the south
and to the immediate east or west is The City of Lag.

rooms.Name: South Lag Way
rooms.Description:
You are now at the City of Lag.  To the north is the temple to the Lag
Gods.  To the North and immediate east and west is the city.  To the South
is the exit to The Land of Lag.

rooms.Name: South Lag Way
rooms.Description:
You are almost there.  The road continues north to spam square.  On either
side of the square is The City of Lag.  In the distance you can see a large
castle.

rooms.Name: South Lag Way
rooms.Description:
As you head down the street you wonder if you are ever going to get there.  
The Street continues to the north and south from here.  The houses are not
quite as far appart as they were before.

rooms.Name: The Post Office
rooms.Description:
The post office in The Land of Lag is not the best place to send your mail.
In fact, if you could mail your mail here at all it would be a surprise.
The building is falling down and the post master looks as if he has been here
for a loooooooooooooong time.

rooms.Name: Entrance to The Land of Lag
rooms.Description:
Welcolme to The Land of Lag!  Everything here moves a little slowly, . . .
well, except the spam.  You see a large golden structure with a tower in the
distance ahead of you.  Even further in the distance the outline of a castle
can be seen to the northwest.

rooms.Name: A Valley of Lag
rooms.Description:
AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAARGH!!!!!! LAAAAAAAAAAAAAG!!!!!!!!!! You have fallen
into a valey of lag.  Your terminal freezes up and you will just have to
wait for it to go away.  Luckily it will only be for one or two ticks this
time =)

rooms.Name: A Dark Pathway
rooms.Description:
You continue on your journey until you come to a fork in the road.
Decisions, decisions, decisions . . . hmmmmmmm.  Which way to go?

rooms.Name: A Dark Pathway
rooms.Description:
You head along a dark pathway through the wilderness.  You are having trouble
seeing where you are going and almost trip.  You continue along the path
hoping that you will find something good.

rooms.Name: A Path Around the Valley
rooms.Description:
This path leads around the valley of lag.  The birds are chirping as you
make your way around the valley.  You notice that there is a nice view of
the City from up here.

rooms.Name: A Path Around the Valley
rooms.Description:
This path leads around the valley of lag.  As the animals play and the birds
chirp you get a warm fuzzy feeling.  You notice the wonderful view of the
city you get from up here.

rooms.Name: East Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You travel down a small paved road.  To the north you hear the sounds of a
blacksmith busy at work.  To the south you hear the sounds of explosions and
the whistle of steam being released from a glass container.  It must be the
shop of a magician.  To the west is spam square and to the east is the cafe
and theater.

rooms.Name: East Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You travel down a paved road.  To the north is the entrance to a small cafe.
To the south is the ticket booth of the theater and spam square is to the
west.

rooms.Name: East Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You are almost at the end of a paved road.  To the north is the entrance to
a small cafe.  To the south is the entrance to the Lag Theater.  If you
travel to the west you will be at lag square.

rooms.Name: East Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You have come to the end of a paved road.  To the south is the entrance to
the Lag Theater and to the north is a small cafe.  If you travel to the
west you will come to lag square, the center of town.

rooms.Name: West Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You are traveling on a large paved road.  To the north is the armory and to
the south is a small grocery store.  To the immediate east is lag square.

rooms.Name: West Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You are traveling on a large paved road.  To the north is the water shop and
to the south the sound of swords and armor crashing can be heard. This must
be the famous Lagmaster's Guild.  If you travel to the east you will reach
spam square.

rooms.Name: West Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You are traveling on a large paved road.  To the north is the large set of
stairs which go up to city hall.  To the south is the infamous Post Office.
If you travel to the east you will reach spam square.

rooms.Name: West Spam Boulevard
rooms.Description:
You are at the end of a large paved road.  To the north is the headquarters
of the City of Lag's Police.  To the south is a small pet shop.  If you
travel to the east you will reach spam square.

rooms.Name: The Weapon Shop
rooms.Description:
You enter the weapon shop.  Weapons of mass destruction and death await your
purchase on the neatly arranged shelves.  A small piece of paper sits on the
counter.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You have entered a small cafe.  There is a lot of singing and drinking going
on.  The cafe is full of vikings and customers from town.  Today's special is
SPAM, just as it is on most days here.  There does not appear to be any tables
left so you head north to the counter.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You have entered a small cafe.  The room is filled with people drinking,
singing, and just having a good time.  There are all sorts of people, from
vikings to people from town.  All of the tables appear to be full so you
go north towards the counter.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You enter a small cafe.  It is full of all sorts of people.  Since there is
no room left at any of the tables you head toward the northwest where there
is a small counter.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are almost completely surrounded by people as you make your way to the 
back of the cafe.  There is a strange smell that is almost like perfume
coming from the west.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are in the center of a small cafe.  You are surrounded by vikings and
drunks!  To the North is the counter and to the south is the entrance
of the cafe.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are in a small cafe.  You head north trying to make your way to the
counter through the crowd of drunks or vikings or both.  To the South is
the entrance to the cafe.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are in a small cafe.  A strong stench is coming from the west.  There
is still a large gathering of drunks and vikings having a great time singing.
To the north is the counter and to the south is the entrance to the cafe.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are in the middle of a small cafe.  To the north is the small counter of
the cafe.  You are in luck as there are a few stools open.  To the south is the
entrance to the cafe.

rooms.Name: A Small Cafe
rooms.Description:
You are in the back of a small cafe.  The counter is to the northwest and
the entrance is to the south.  A large wooden door stands to your north.

rooms.Name: At the Counter
rooms.Description:
You are at the counter.  The smell of freshly cooked spam rises from the
steaming grills.  You wonder what the menue looks like, but think that it
would be better if you didn't know.  To the south is the entrance to the
cafe.

rooms.Name: At the Counter
rooms.Description:
You are at the counter.  There are a few extera stools here so you decide
to take a seat and join in the singing.  You immediately know you have made
a mistake and realize it would be safer if you just watched.  To the south
is the entrance to the cafe.

rooms.Name: The Manager's Office
rooms.Description:
You have entered the office of the manager.  It is painted a light blue
color and has a small artificial plant in the northwest corner.  The
frayed grey carpet almost falls apart as you walk on it.  To the south is
the small cafe.

rooms.Name: The Men's Room
rooms.Description:
PEEEEEEEE-U!!!!!!! It stinks in here.  It does not look as if anyone has
cleaned this room since dinosaurs roamed the earth!  Toilet paper litters
the floor and the sink is coated with a thick black grime.  It would
probably be a good idea to head east back into the cafe.

rooms.Name: Lady's Room
rooms.Description:
This room is not nearly as bad as the mens room.  Luckily the cafe decided
to hire a janitor to fix up some some things, including the rest rooms.  Good
thing you didn't come here yesturday.  To the east is the small cafe.

rooms.Name: The Ticket Booth
rooms.Description:
You hav entered a small ticket booth.  You can buy tickets to the next movie
in the Lag Theater here.  You are kind of afraid of what a movie would look
like in The Land of Lag.  To the north is east spam boulevard.

rooms.Name: Theater Entrance
rooms.Description:
You push your way through a small line and make your way into the theater
You must pass through the large revolving glass door and hand the usher
your ticket.  To the south is the theater lobby and to the north is east
spam boulevard

rooms.Name: Theater Entrance
rooms.Description:
You push your way through the small line and make your way into the theater
You must pass through a large revolving glass door and hand the usher your
ticket.  To the south is the theater lobby and to the north is east spam
boulevard.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are in the front of a large lobby.  People are wandering around buying
food and playing the arcade games to the west.  The entrance to the
theater is to the northeast and the smell of popcorn is coming from the
southeast.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are in the front of a large lobby.  People are wandering around buying
all sorts of food and candy.  The smell of popcorn and other movie snacks
is coming from the south.  The entrance to the theater is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are in the front of the lobby.  People are wandering around buying
food and candy.  The smell of freshly buttered popcorn is coming from the
southwest.  The theater entrance is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are now in the middle of the lobby.  The smell of popcorn and pretzels
comes from the east.  The crowd is slowly starting to move south because
the movie is about to start.

rooms.Name: Consessions
rooms.Description:
You see a long white counter with all sorts of food and candy behind it.  The
counter continues to the the south from here and the entrance to the theater
is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are now in the middle of the lobby.  The smell of popcorn and pretzels
comes from the west.  The crowd is slowly starting to move south because the
movie is about to start.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are in the middle of the lobby.  The smell of freshly buttered popcorn
and warm pretzels comes from the the east.  The crowd continues it's way
south into the theater.

rooms.Name: Concessions
rooms.Description:
You see a long white counter with all sorts of food and candy behind it.
The counter continues to the north and the entrance to the movie hall is
south of here.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are in the middle of the lobby.  The smell of freshly buttered popcorn
and warm pretzels comes from the west.  People are still moving to the south
hoping to get a good seat in the movie hall before it starts.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are now in the back of the lobby.  The lights are slowly being turned
down and people are scrambeling to their seats.  The entrance to the movie
hall is to the southeast and the smell of popcorn is coming from the
northeast.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are now in the back of the lobby.  The crowd is slowly pushing it's way
south as the lights are being turned down.  The wonderful smell of movie
popcorn is coming from the north.

rooms.Name: The Lobby
rooms.Description:
You are now in the back of the lobby.  The crowd is scrambeling to the
southwest as the lights in the movie hall are slowly turned down. The
wonder smell of freshly buttered popcorn comes from the northwest.

rooms.Name: The Manager's Office
rooms.Description:
You enter a small business office.  There are no windows in this room and
it seems to be very boring.  The walls and carpet are grey with navy blue
patterns and the pictures on the wall look like they came with the frame.
The lobby is to the west.

rooms.Name: The Entrance to the Movie Theater
rooms.Description:
As you make your way into the movie theater the lights are almost completely
out.  You scramble forward to find a seat before the movie starts.  The backk of
the theater is to the south and the lobby is to the north.  The sounds of
someone running around can be heard from above.

rooms.Name: The Projection Booth
rooms.Description:
You have entered the projection booth.  This is a very small room where the
the projectionist works.  The movie is running late so everything is a mess!
Film canisters and papers are everywhere.  To the south is the entrance to the
movie theater.

rooms.Name: In the Back of the Theater
rooms.Description:
You are in the back of the movie theater.  It looks kind of crowded but you
see some seats to the south.  The lights are out now and people are starting
to look at their watches since the movie is late as always.  The entrance to
the theater is to the northeast.

rooms.Name: In The Back of the Theater
rooms.Description:
You are in the back of the movie theater.  The lights have just gone
out and people are impatiently waiting for the movie to start.  To the
south there are some empty seats and to the north is the theater
entrance.

rooms.Name: In the Back of the Theater
rooms.Description:
You are in the back of the theater.  The lights have just gone out and
it is difficult to see your way, but it looks like there are some seats
to the south.  The entrance to the movie theater is to the northwest.

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You have moved closer to the front of the theater.  You see a few seats
here, but decide to get a closer look at the movie.  It appears to only
be moving one frame at a time.  The problem is that no one seems to
notice except you.  Since you can not believe your eyes you move
further south.

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You are much closer to the front of the movie theater now.  As the movie
starts you notice something peculiar. The movie is only moving one frame
at a time.  No, it can't be!  You move south to get a closer look.

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You are now much closer to the front of the movie theater.  The movie
has just started and you notice something odd.  The movie is only moving
one frame every one or two seconds.  No, it can't be!  You move south
to get a better look.

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You are very close to the front of the movie theater.  When you try to ask
someone what is wrong all you get is a loud SHHHHHH from the people in the
theater.  You continue south in hopes of finding out what is wrong with the
movie

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You are now very close to the front of the movie theater.  When you try
to ask someone what is wrong with the movie, all you get is a resounding
SHHHHHH!!! from the people in the theater.  You decide to go to the front
of the theater in search of an answer.

rooms.Name: In the Middle
rooms.Description:
You are very close to the front of the movie theater.  When you ask
someone what is wrong with the movie you get a resounding SHHHHHH
from the rest of the people watching the movie.  You decide to go
further south to find out what is wrong.

rooms.Name: In the Front
rooms.Description:
You are now in the front of the movie theater.  You can not believe
your eyes, the movie is only moving a frame every one or two seconds!
Laaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaag!!!!!!!  You decide that it is not worth it and
leave to the north.

rooms.Name: In the Front
rooms.Description:
You have made your way to the front of the theater.  When you get here
you still can not believe your eyes.  The movie is only moving a frame
every one or two seconds.  Laaaaaaaaaaaaag!!!!!!!!! You get frustrated
and decide to leave to the north.

rooms.Name: In the Front
rooms.Description:
You are now at the front of the theater.  You rub your eyes and look at
the screen again.  No, it can't be!!!! Laaaaaaaaaaaaag!!!!!!  You decide
that it isn't even worth watching and leave to the north.

rooms.Name: The Great Lagini's
rooms.Description:
You have entered the shop of The Great Lagini.  It is an old shop with
stone walls and a wooden roof.  Potions, scrolls, and wands line the
walls on shelves.  A counter with a list on it sits in the middle of
the room.

rooms.Name: The Armory
rooms.Description:
You are in the shop cluttered with all sorts of armor.  Large stone
shelves line the walls of the tiny shop.  You notice a large counter
on the west side of the room with a small piece of paper on it.

rooms.Name: The Water Shop
rooms.Description:
You have entered a busy shop off of west spam boulevard.  The main
food of this town is spam which is so darn salty that everyone comes
here for a quick drink.  A piece of paper sits on a small red counter
on the east side of the room.

rooms.Name: The Lobby of City Hall
rooms.Description:
You are now in the large lobby of The Land of Lag's city hall.
The large ceiling has elaborate pictures of the founding of the city.
The walls are a light green color to match the paintings.  The Mayor's
office is to the east and the council's chamber is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Mayor's office
rooms.Description:
You are now in Mayor Bob's office.  There is a large desk in the center of
the room covered with thousands of papers.  You notice the pretty rose color
of the ceiling and walls.  To the west is the loby of city hall.

rooms.Name: The Council's Chamber
rooms.Description:
You are now in the chamber of the city council.  Several members sit at the
large oak table.  Several of the large red chairs, however, remain empty.
The meeting is about to come to order so they better hurry!

rooms.Name: The Council's Chamber
rooms.Description:
The council meeting is about to begin.  Several late members rush through
the door as the President's wooden gavel strikes the table.  All is silent
as the president clears his throat to begin.

rooms.Name: The Council's Chamber
rooms.Description:
You are now in the back of the council chamber.  To the north is a small
window and an air conditioning unit.  You wait for the chamber to quiet
down so the President can begin the meeting.

rooms.Name: The Council's Chamber
rooms.Description:
The council is sitting and talking while the President of the council
impatiently waits for them to quiet down.  Some are even staring out the
small window to the north, wishing that they were somewhere else.

rooms.Name: The Entrance to the Police Station
rooms.Description:
You walk up a small set of stone stairs which lead up to the police
station.  The police station is small and it has a small staff.  There is
not much need for a police station since the crime rate here is so low.
You enter the police station through a large set of black doors.

rooms.Name: The Police Station
rooms.Description:
You have entered a room with solid white walls and bright lights.  To the
east and west are prison cells in the event that there should actually be
a crime.  To the north is the office of the chief of police

rooms.Name: A Holding Cell
rooms.Description:
You are now in a room with stone walls and cold iron bars for a door.
This is where all of the prisoners are kept before they are taken away
to a larger jail.  Since there are not that many crimes commited in the
Land of Lag they usually just stay here.

rooms.Name: A Holding Cell
rooms.Description:
You enter a room with stone walls and cold iron bars for a door.  The
prisoners would be taken to a larger jail after being sentenced, but there
is no need for that due to the low crime rate.

rooms.Name: The Chief's Office
rooms.Description:
The Chief's office is painted blue and has a large picture window on the
north wall.  His hat rests on a small dresser on the west side of the room
To the south is the main room of the police station.

rooms.Name: The Pet Shop
rooms.Description:
The pet shop is new and just opened up recently.  There are hundreds of cages
with animals in them lining the walls.  The pets, however, are kind of strange
here.  They are not your usual cats, dogs, or even wolf, but they will serve
you well.  A piece of paper rests on a small blue counter.

rooms.Name: Room for pets to load
rooms.Description:
Hiya all,
Just a place for the mobs in the pet shop to load =)

rooms.Name: Entrance To the Lag Guild
rooms.Description:
You must walk inbetween two giant marble pillars to enter the lagmaster's
guild.  Two giant golden knights stand guard over the gate.  Only a true
master of lag may pass.  Since you are here you are probably going to end
up fighting them to get in. =)

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Guild
rooms.Description:
You have entered the main room of the lagmaster's guild.  It has large glass
skylights and a huge arena in the center of it.  Here the lagmaster's fight
and practice for their neverending battle against their evil foe LAG!!!!!
To the south is the lagmaster's dining hall, to the east is the office of
the grand lagmaster, and the entrance is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Waiting Room of the Grand Lagmaster
rooms.Description:
The waiting room of the grand lagmaster has a small table with all sorts
of magazines on it.  The walls are a plain brown color and the floor is
made of wood.  The main room of the lagmaster's guild is to the west.

rooms.Name: The Office of the Grand Lagmaster
rooms.Description:
You are now in a large office with blue walls and white trim.  You notice the
pictures of the grand lag masters previous kills hanging on the wall.  You
also notice the mess of papers and office supplies scattered all over his
beautiful wooden desk.

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Dining Hall
rooms.Description:
This is the largest room in the guild.  Lagmasters can be seen in every
direction eating, drinking and, in general, having a good time.  You
notice the many beautiful waitresses wandering through the hall.  The
exit to the hall is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Dining Hall
rooms.Description:
This is the largest room in the guild.  Lagmasters can be seen in every
direction eating, drinking and, in general, having a good time.  You
notice the many beautiful waitresses wandering through the hall.  The
exit to the hall is to the west and north.

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Dining Hall
rooms.Description:
This is the largest room in the guild.  Lagmasters can be seen in every
direction eating, drinking and, in general, having a good time.  You
notice the many beautiful waitresses wandering through the hall.  The
exit to the hall is to the west and north.

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Dining Hall
rooms.Description:
This is the largest room in the guild.  Lagmasters can be seen in every
direction eating, drinking and, in general, having a good time.  You
notice the many beautiful waitresses wandering through the hall.  The
exit to the hall is to the north.

rooms.Name: The Lagmaster's Dining Hall
rooms.Description:
This is the largest room in the guild.  Lagmasters can be seen in every
direction eating, drinking and, in general, having a good time.  You
notice the many beautiful waitresses wandering through the hall.  The
exit to the hall is to the west and north.
